Paris Saint-Germain manager, Mauricio Pochettino, has announced his side’s squad to tackle Barcelona in the Champions League round of 16 first-leg on Tuesday night at Camp Nou. Pochettino released a 22-man squad to face Barcelona in a post via PSG’s official website on Monday. PSG head to the game following a 2-1 win over Nice in the French Ligue encounter over the weekend, while Barcelona defeated Alaves 5-1 in the LaLiga. PSG’s squad against Barcelona: BAKKER Mitchel, DIALLO Abdou, DRAXLER Julian, FLORENZI Alessandro, GUEYE Idrissa, HERRERA Ander, ICARDI Mauro, KEAN Moise, KEHRER Thilo, KIMPEMBE Presnel, KURZAWA Layvin, LETELLIER Alexandre, MARQUINHOS, MBAPPÉ Kylian, MICHUT Edouard, NAVAS Keylor, PAREDES Leandro, PEREIRA Danilo, RAFINHA, RICO Sergio, SARABIA Pablo, VERRATTI Marco MISSING from PSG’s squad: BERNAT Juan, DAGBA Colin, DI MARIA Angel, FRANCHI Denis, NEYMAR JR, PEMBÉLÉ Timothée, SIMONS Xavi. The kick-off time for the match is 9 pm, Nigerian time.